docs.abstract: Ahead of a major five-city show, the artist reflects on the evolution of her practice and her distrust of Amazon.
docs.snippet: Ahead of a major five-city show, the artist reflects on the evolution of her practice and her distrust of Amazon.
docs.lead_paragraph: This past December, I met the abstract artist Rochelle Feinstein at her studio — a 900-square-foot space in an industrial office building in Queens, N.Y. — to discuss her upcoming exhibition, “You Again,” a survey of her work that will be displayed simultaneously in six independent galleries in Paris, Zurich, New York, Miami and Los Angeles, beginning this month at Bridget Donahue and Candice Madey in Manhattan. Unlike many painters, the ineffability of personal experience concerns Feinstein less than the cultural conditions that create it. What interests her is, “How can I enter that cultural condition and how can I enter it right now?”

headline.main: Rochelle Feinstein Makes Work That Is Purposefully Hard to Define

docs.abstract: An Amazon program guaranteed sellers a minimum price while offering a potential upside if an algorithm determined that customers were willing to pay more
docs.snippet: An Amazon program guaranteed sellers a minimum price while offering a potential upside if an algorithm determined that customers were willing to pay more
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon settled a price-fixing investigation by the Washington State attorney general’s office on Wednesday, agreeing to pay $2.25 million and end a program that gave it control over the prices of products supplied by third-party sellers on its marketplace.

headline.main: Amazon pays $2.25 million to settle a price-fixing investigation.

docs.abstract: The states argue that Google reached a deal with Facebook to have the social network join its effort in an effort to “kill” a competing ad network.

docs.lead_paragraph: Google’s chief executive approved an agreement with Facebook at the heart of an antitrust lawsuit that 16 states and Puerto Rico have lodged against the search giant, according to a portion of the complaint revealed on Friday.

headline.main: Google’s chief executive signed off on deal at center of antitrust case, states say.

docs.abstract: With midterm elections approaching, a vote taken on Thursday could be the first of several that Congress takes on bills aimed at the industry.
docs.snippet: With midterm elections approaching, a vote taken on Thursday could be the first of several that Congress takes on bills aimed at the industry.
docs.lead_paragraph: Lawmakers on Capitol Hill are readying a major push on bills aimed at restraining the power of the country’s biggest tech companies, as they see the window of opportunity closing quickly ahead of the midterm elections.

headline.main: Efforts to Rein In Big Tech May Be Running Out of Time
